results.name: If C is a doubly-even binary code of length N=24m+n, 1 <= n <= 24, then the minimum distance of C^perp is bounded above by 4m+a(n).
comment: Coincides with beginning of A066016, although of course that sequence is infinite.
link: E. M. Rains, Bounds for self-dual codes over Z_4, Finite Fields Appl. 6 (2000), 146-163.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Sep 13 2004
